Text: Farewell Happy Hour for Jamie Ginsberg Cc Gentlemen In celebration of Jamie Ginsbergs new job and to say farewell prior to her impending departure we are going to have one mother of a happy hour Save the evening of July th Thursday to meet for a drink or so and to see Jamie off to NYC The Timberwolf on Bissonnet will be the place and the event will start at PM It will peak at around midnight and go downhill from there Please join me on the th so that we can give Jamie the royal sendoff that she deserves No need to RSVP just show up when you can Once again the location is THE TIMBERWOLF on Bissonnet just east of Kirby The time and date are PM on July Bryan Garrett Global Bandwidth Trading Enron Broadband Services Phone Mobile wwwenronnet

FW Touch FootballPST Original Appointment From Garrett Bryan Sent Wednesday November PM To Garrett Bryan Ahad Farhad Andre Carin Arnold Matthew Barnes Corbin Bogucki Robert Carpino Neil Case David Chen Will Curry Mike Day Justin Dolezal Regan Enochs Fred Freeman Ben Frey Gunnar Hawthorn Jay Heintzelman Pete Herron Chris Hough Greg Irani Eric Jachimiak Matthew Lindvall Tim Manuel Scott Martinez Roberto W Masani Zal Mathews Reagan McDonald Rob Miralles Albert Mujumdar Ravi Noble Ted Paysse Juan Carlos Rogers Benjamin Santikos Mark Schneider Richard Schultz Ethan Shulklapper Ken Simpson Erik Simson Kyle Spector Brian Stadler Gary Suarez John Synnott Ryan Terp Brian Thames Davis Thibodeaux Ryan Tull Ryan Vaughn Kevin Walsh David Will Nathan Woods Trevor Woulfe Greg Zimmerman Grant Subject Touch Football When Sunday December AM PM GMT Central Time US Canada Where Rice University see attached map Guys Come on out this Sunday and take out some of your frustrations on the field We will have beer this time so be prepared to have a few Forward this on to anyone else you can think of whod like to play Were having a touch football game this Sunday the nd at Rice The attached map indicates the place where you should park small white box with X in it and where the game will take place larger white box nearby Game time is AM and well play until whenever everyone gets tired and goes home Teams will be picked on site There are several fields adjacent to one another so we can play two games simultaneously if we have too many people for one game I will bring two footballs and some cones for field boundaries Please feel free to bring other equipment as you see fit eg footballs cones flags other if you have them Cleats are recommended if you own them already and if not go pick up a pair at Academy for Please bring your own waterfoodbeerother refreshments Rice U Map for Flag Footballgif
